 BY AGNES NWORIE, ABAKALIKI Ahead of 2023 general elections, Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State has threatened to sack all local government Council chairmen in the state whose council records low number of registrated voters. Umahi gave the warning during this week’s executive council meeting in preparation for the next year’s elections and advised  the people not to support Labour Party because the state alledgely belong to APC party. The governor who is not visibly happy with the outcome of the just concluded APC presidential primaries stated that the only bargaining power remaining is to ensure that greater number of Ebonyians have their PVCs ready for the forthcoming general elections stressing Ebonyi State can never support the Labour Party . He regretted that the leadership of Ohaneze Ndigbo failed to galvanized opinions, making  statement towards Igbo Presidency which undermined the level of support gotten by  candidates from South East during the election. He added that his current major focus  is Ebonyi agenda and has no business with Ohaneze. The governor also used the opportunity at the EXCO to inuagurate new Head of Service, Rita Mary Okoro and five new  Commissioners to fill the vacant positions created in the EXCO as a result of the resignation of some members who left to pursue their various political ambitions. 